            <biogHist>
                <p>Alexander MacNeil was born to Roderick and Mary née MacIntyre. The 1841 Census
                    records him living in Brèibhig with his wife Mary née MacDougall and five
                    children: Catherine (13), Mary (10), John (8), Isabella (6), and Christy (3).
                    Alexander was a farm labourer and his wife a weaver. By 1851 he had moved to
                    Gleann with his wife and children, John and Marion (8). In 1861 he had moved to
                    Kentangaval with his wife and three children, Mary, John and Marion, plus his
                    granddaughter Mary MacKinnon. The Census indicates they were living in a house
                    without windows.</p>
                <p>MacNeill and his wife remained in Kentangaval, with their daughters Isabella and
                    Marion, and grandchildren Mary MacKinnon and Alexander Keny, with the 1871
                    Census recording the house as now having a window. The 1881 Census records the
                    same grandchildren still living together, with Alexander and Mary, together with
                    their daughter Isabella in a house now with two windows. By this time Alexander
                    and Mary were paupers. Not long after the Census both Alexander and Mary, now
                    aged 94 and 95, died. Alexander died in September 1881 from senile disability
                    and Mary in September 1881 with the same diagnosis. Their daughter Isabella
                    signed the death certificates.</p>
                <p>Carmichael met MacNeil several times and collected stories from him. </p>
